 of hope for success.  It takes on the form of a small raid that requires time to get people there, get them organized, move them through, etc.<br>
<br>
This is not something that many of the smaller guilds can just whip up on a moments notice (in fact, it often takes members from a few of the small guilds to successfully pull stuff like this off - which requires even MORE prep, time and coordination).<br>
<br>
In my opinion, things like the CoM Reaver run <br>
*should* be reserved so that I can be reasonably assured that when we get all of these people there at then date and time we need them, the Reavers will be there waiting with open, chunky, mean, nasty black arms.<br>
<br>
As far as placing a reservation on the board for these things - I have placed the time that we will be there so that other people can hunt as long as they want realizing that we will need at least a 2 hour re-spawn time (if they have been killing Reavers) before we get there.<br>
<br>
If you have no problem throwing a group together on the spur of the moment to go kill - more power to you!  No reservation needed!  Just please make sure that you check the board before you go so that you don't stomp the Reavers for those of us who DO have it reserved. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
