<br><a href="http://www.rutabaga-paradox.org/reject.html">4 Easy Steps To Getting Your Uber Guild Application Rejected On The Legends Server</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uaanadien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aanadien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Opinionated</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/17/02 10:01:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1089.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.vanessarussell.com/Phank/jumppavitarsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reserving CoM Reavers?  Discuss</span><hr size=1> &quot;I think posting intentions is just a polite thing to do.&quot;<br>
<br>
How is it polite?  Are you doing ME a favor somehow by posting your intentions?<br>
<br>
Maybe.  If you're posting to let me know that, should I show up Wednesday night, I'll find the reavers camped, then thanks.  That's polite.<br>
<br>
If, however, you're posting to let me know that should I be working reavers on wednesday night, you'll be showing up expecting me to yield the site to you, then that's not polite at all.  That's just dressing a reservation up in a funny hat and pretending it's something else.<br>
<br>
It's certainly true that 2 high-end toons can kill reavers but it can take a few groups at lower levels.<br>
<br>
But you don't see anyone posting reservations for the ghoul lord, and it'd probably take more than one group of 40s to do him.<br>
<br>
So if we're arguing that any mob that takes multiple groups of characters of SOME level should be reserved, that pretty much opens it up for everything on down to level-5 mobs in newbie zones.<br>
<br>
The problem this leads to is demonstrated by Marics post.  &quot;The strength of reservations is only as strong as those that honor them.&quot;  The idea being that if I'm at, say, VL ledge with an XP crew, and some twits who &quot;reserved&quot; the ledge on the board roll up on me and tell me to beat it, _I_ am somehow the bad guy.<br>
<br>
Essentially, this is an attempt, intentional or not, to kill the system with kindness.  The system works only as long as most folks respect the reservations.  So if you use it to reserve stupid shit that nobody's gonna take seriously, people like Maric are soon running around saying that &quot;XXX didn't respect my reservation of the left-side KC zone-in, so why should I respect PA's reservation of Hateplane?&quot;  And then the system starts to fall apart.<br>
<br>
There's an obvious consensus that Hateplane is suitable for reservations and that D'vinn is not.  Where's the line?<br>
<br>
I think the line is somewhere ABOVE CoM reavers.  Wanna take a poll and find out?  Not a poll poll, but a voting thread where people sign their bloody names and you can't spam up a bogus vote tally.  I bet the votes will run pretty heavily against lumping CoM reavers in with Hate.<br>
<br>
And if I'm wrong and there's a genuine consensus that Reavers are a reservation-worthy camp, I'll happily honor any CoM reservation.<br>
